Chelsea football club of England star Christian Pulisic has become the first ever United States of America national team player to set a new record, after netting a classic goal in his team’s 3-0 away victory over Leeds United football club.
The former Borussia Dortmund football club of Germany star retained his spot in the away team’s attacking midfield, and he was able to perform excellently in the game.
Christian Pulisic led Chelsea’s attack alongside Romelu Lukaku and his fellow Chelsea Academy product Mason Mount, and they were able to guide the team to a well deserved victory.
Mason Mount broke the deadlock for the Blues in the 4th minutes and Christian Pulisic doubled the lead in the 55th minutes before Romelu Lukaku netted the last goal of the game in the 83rd minutes to end the match 3-0.
Pulisic was fantastic for the Blues throughout the game, and he was able to score a goal in his team’s well deserved victory.
With Christian Pulisic’s goal against Leeds United football club, it means he has set a new record in the English Premier League.
“Christian Pulisic’s goal against Leeds United is the first time in English Premier League history that an American has scored against a team coached by an American.”
The midfield maestro will now be looking forward to continuing his impressive performance for the Blues when they play Liverpool football club in the final of this season’s Emirates FA Cup at Wembley Stadium on Sunday.


